{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4d986820-250e-4a64-86c4-c810d2c5f047","content":"The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them. It can't help with post-mortem investigation.\n\nHere's how you can analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n**Using LLDB + SOS** (Linux):\n```bash\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n# or\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\n\n**Using WinDbg** (Windows):\nOpen the dump, load SOS (`!analyze -v`, `!clrstack`, `!pe`).\n\nWould you like me to walk you through running any of these tools on your dump file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7ecc0523-5888-4d51-9797-97227980d11d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description specifically says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is NOT appropriate here since the user wants to analyze a dump, not collect one.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their crash dump.","outputTokens":390,"requestId":"6088:C5472:2FD68C:3E85A5:69FFE5B5"},"id":"d27b856b-58ee-40a9-a719-a5bf5c50aadb","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:56:16.860Z","parentId":"2f4c087f-fc30-4a93-a23a-18afe00f8b74"}
